    "title": "Real-Time Streaming Attribution: Sub-Second Event Processing with Apache Kafka and Flink",
    "doi": "10.5281/zenodo.18860342",
    "publication_date": "2026-03-04",
    "description": "Marketing attribution has historically been a batch process \u2014 events accumulate, models run overnight, and decisions are made on yesterday's data. This paper presents a streaming attribution architecture built on Apache Kafka and Apache Flink that processes attribution events in under 100ms. The framework integrates stateful stream processing, windowed aggregation, and real-time Shapley calculation to enable millisecond-latency attribution decisions for live bidding and budget optimization. Provides infrastructure foundation for Robinson (2026a) through (2026f).",
